var rotateString = function(s, goal) {
    if (s.length !== goal.length) return false;
    return (s + s).includes(goal);
};



String Rotation – Notes
Problem: Check if string s can become goal after left shifts
Condition: Length of s and goal must be equal
Key Idea: goal should be a substring of s + s
Steps
Check if lengths are equal, else return false
Create new string: temp = s + s
Check if goal exists in temp
Code Idea
(s + s).includes(goal)
Example
s = "abcde"
goal = "cdeab"
s + s = "abcdeabcde" → contains goal
Final Rule
Rotation possible if goal is substring of s + s
